values: I've been here for 2 and a half weeks, and I hate it.  I've been depressed since I've moved here.  This sucks, and I don't want to be here any more.  I want to go back with my friends.

It's official, I am officially moved into my new enviornment.  Things have just been going down hill since I found out about the move.  I talked to my girlfriend.  I love her to death, but we both have doubts about our relationship with us being that far away.  I would do anything for her, and she knows this, but at the same time I am so far away from her, and I can't be there for her.  That isn't fair to her.  She needs someone who can be there for her when she needs them.  Not someone that she will have to wait to see until they can find time to come back to her.  It was the hardest decision that I have ever made.  I told her all of that, and it was so hard.  I cried as I told her, and she cried and just layed in my arms.  I felt so helpless, and at that very moment, so alone.  She was pretty much my whole life, and I just never realized it.  I never knew how much I really cared about her, until I had to let her go.  Until I had to let her go on and find someone she can really be with.  Someone who is physically there to support her when she needs it.

Since than I just havn't felt like going out.  My guys threw me one hell of a going away party, but I just didn't really get into to it too much.  My last day with Julie was the best/worst day of my life.  It was something that I don't want to forget, but at the same time I want to forget all of the pain I had that day.  I want to get rid of all of this pain I feel right now.  I don't want to feel alone, and she was the only person that it feels like was keeping me alive.  Not litterally, but with my emotions.  It's just so hard.  I love her so much, and I miss all of my friends, but right now she is the only person that I can think of.  The only person that I didn't want to leave for good.  Maybe after I get a decent job out here, and save up money, I can move back there.  Back there to be with her.  I won't get my hopes up to high.  She might have found someone else by than.  I can't go back there to find that out.  I can't even talk to her on the phone or online right now.  It's just too hard.  Too hard to know that I just left the love of my life.  I was trying to block all of it out.  The fact that I knew I would have to do this when I left, and I just didn't want to think of it.

So... In my last entry... as most of you know... I found out that I may be moving to Ohio.  Well, that chance is very well good.  My parents found a place out there, and I was there over the weekend, and it was just so lonely out there.  I have no one.  No one to share my thoughts with, no one to talk to, just no one to go out be a dumbass with, and have a good time.  No more music with my boys, no more parties.  No more getting drunk with my close friends, and random sex with girls I don't even know.  Well, I'm sure that will happen again.  Atleast the sex part haha... but there is nothing for me there.  Nothing to peak my interests, and I have to move out there if they close the deal on that house.  If I do go though, there is going to be one hell of a party that way, no one will EVER forget me.

I found out that I might be moving within the next few months.  It's not like a normal move where you move 3 streets away from where you live now, but It's more like 3 states or so away from where I live now.  My dad got a job offer in Ohio, so I might have to move with him there, unless my friends want to go in on an apartment with me.  Let's hope they do.

I hate reading people's journal's and all they do is try to get attention and sympathy out of people, OR you read the journals or read something in their journal, and you know this person is a poser.  Fucking be real people, and stop crying out for attention...

I don't use this thing enough.  Well, I went out and got all kinds of fucked up the other night, and went on stage for the performance.  Did pretty well, and than after that I went out with the guys, and got even worse than I already was.  I was so smoked out before we even started the show.  After we went out and got drunk and did shrooms, and smoked more.  My night was so crazy!

I havn't updated in a while... Our band is doing great, and we might be going on tour this summer...  We're not completly sure if that's what we all want yet, but there is a good possibility that we will.

First entry, and I want anyone who reads this that finds me interesting in any way to add me.  I want to meet new people who like to do what I do, or people that have the same interests. 

First off, I'm one of the biggest pot heads you'll find.  Anything you can smoke out of, I got it.  I'm in a band, and we're not bad.  That's not just from my point, others have told us this, and it rocks!  I play guitar, bass guitar.  I broke up with my girlfriend a couple weeks ago.  Well, it was more like a mutual thing, but I was the one that brought it up.  We both felt like we were going out seperate ways, and she felt like I didn't have time for her when it came to my band, which I don't understand, because I was with her all the time, whenever she wanted me to.  Oh well,  it still hurts and I'm getting over it.  I might have brought it up, and it might have been mutual, but that doesn't mean that it doesn't hurt.  I just gotta look into my future, and hopefully get this band thing on the go.

Well looks like I have to go to practice...  fun fun...

Rock on and keep it real,

Frank
